      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Add plugin task lifecycle API",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nPlugins can inspect task runs today, but they do not have a narrow public SDK path for creating a plugin-owned task run, reporting progress, and finalizing the run while preserving owner/session scoping. That leaves plugin task lifecycle behavior either unavailable or tied to internal core task APIs that are not safe for third-party plugin contracts.\n\nThis PR adds a plugin-safe task run lifecycle API under `api.runtime.tasks.runs.bindSession(...).lifecycle` / `fromToolContext(...).lifecycle`. Plugin-created records are stored as existing `cli` task runtime rows with a required plugin-namespaced `taskKind`, and task creation identity now includes `taskKind` so same-owner/same-run records with different plugin task kinds stay separated.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Adds a plugin-safe task run lifecycle API under `api.runtime.tasks.runs.bindSession(...).lifecycle` / `fromToolContext(...).lifecycle`.\n- Creates plugin-owned records as existing `cli` task runtime rows with required plugin-namespaced `taskKind`.\n- Adds owner-scoped exact create/progress/finalize behavior and exposes `taskKind` in task run DTOs.\n- Documents plugin-owned task records and SDK lifecycle usage.\n\n## Evidence\n\nFocused validation:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/tasks/task-registry.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  71 passed (71)\n```\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/runtime/runtime-tasks.test.ts src/plugins/runtime/index.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  29 passed (29)\n```\n\n```text\n$ pnpm plugin-sdk:api:check\nOK docs/.generated/plugin-sdk-api-baseline.sha256\n```\n\n```text\n$ pnpm check:changed\n[check:changed] lanes=core, coreTests, extensions, extensionTests, docs\nFound 0 warnings and 0 errors.\nruntime-sidecar-loaders: local runtime sidecar loaders look OK.\nImport cycle check: 0 runtime value cycle(s).\n```\n\nAdditional checks run:\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 <touched files>`\n- `pnpm check:docs`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nRedacted real runtime lifecycle proof at PR head `95cedbf4558905e68f351613f71fe7640df5b69e`, using `createRuntimeTaskRuns().bindSession(...).lifecycle` with an isolated temp state dir:\n\n```text\n$ pnpm tsx --eval '<runtime lifecycle create/progress/finalize proof script>'\n{\n  \"created\": {\n    \"runtime\": \"cli\",\n    \"sessionKey\": \"agent:proof:telegram:group:redacted\",\n    \"ownerKey\": \"agent:proof:telegram:group:redacted\",\n    \"taskKind\": \"proof-plugin.session\",\n    \"sourceId\": \"proof-plugin\",\n    \"runId\": \"proof-run-redacted\",\n    \"status\": \"running\",\n    \"progressSummary\": \"created\"\n  },\n  \"progressed\": {\n    \"runtime\": \"cli\",\n    \"taskKind\": \"proof-plugin.session\",\n    \"runId\": \"proof-run-redacted\",\n    \"status\": \"running\",\n    \"progressSummary\": \"progressed\"\n  },\n  \"finalized\": {\n    \"runtime\": \"cli\",\n    \"taskKind\": \"proof-plugin.session\",\n    \"runId\": \"proof-run-redacted\",\n    \"status\": \"succeeded\",\n    \"progressSummary\": \"progressed\",\n    \"terminalSummary\": \"finalized\"\n  },\n  \"sameKindReuse\": {\n    \"sameTaskId\": true,\n    \"taskKind\": \"proof-plugin.session\",\n    \"runId\": \"proof-run-redacted\"\n  },\n  \"differentTaskKindSeparation\": {\n    \"differentTaskId\": true,\n    \"firstTaskKind\": \"proof-plugin.session\",\n    \"secondTaskKind\": \"proof-plugin.other\",\n    \"sharedRunId\": \"proof-run-redacted\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis proves create, progress, finalize, same-kind reuse, and different-`taskKind` separation through the public plugin runtime lifecycle API.\n\n## Known Base Failure\n\n- `pnpm test:changed` routes `src/plugins/loader.test.ts` and fails `loadOpenClawPlugins > does not re-register non-bundled plugins after gateway-bindable boot loads` with expected `1`, received `2`.\n- The same failure reproduces on a fresh `origin/main` worktree at `9e01d19db3`, so it is not introduced by this PR.\n",
        "branch": "codex/plugin-task-lifecycle",
